all.data <- read.csv("./databases/all_data.csv", header = TRUE)

all.data$Timestamp <- force_tz(ymd_hms(all.data$Timestamp), tz = "America/New_York") #Reads in timestamp as integer, so converts to POSIXct

if(class(all.data$Sensor_ID) != "factor"){
  all.data$Sensor_ID <- sapply(all.data$Sensor_ID, as.factor)
}

dist.data <- group_by(all.data, Sensor_ID)
sensors <- levels(dist.data$Sensor_ID)

#Separate density plots with both bars and lines
for(i in 1 : length(sensors)){
  start.row <- grep(sensors[i], dist.data$Sensor_ID)[1]
  if(i < length(sensors)){
    end.row <- grep(sensors[i+1], dist.data$Sensor_ID)[1] - 1
  }
  else{
    end.row <- length(dist.data$Sensor_ID)
  }
  print(ggplot(dist.data[start.row:end.row,], aes(x = ParticulateMatter)) +
          geom_histogram(aes(y = ..density..), color = "black", fill = "white") +
          geom_density(alpha = .25, fill = "red") +
          labs(title = sensors[i], x = "PM-2.5 Conc. (\u03BCg/m\u00B3)", y = "Frequency") +
          xlim(0, 200))
}
